ts - 100xengineers on April 2, 2026: &quot;Someone built a tool that jailbreaks 55 major AI models and fits it into a single HTML file.\n\nIt&#039;s called G0DM0D3, built by a guy called Pliny the Liberator, a self-taught hacker with zero coding background who TIME magazine named one of the 100 most influential people in AI.\n\nHere&#039;s what it actually does.\n\nYou type one prompt. It fires that same prompt at up to 55 AI models simultaneously, ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, Grok, all of them, and races them against each other.\n\nAny model that refuses, hedges, or adds a disclaimer? Penalized.\n\nThe one that gives the most direct, complete answer? Wins. That&#039;s the response you see.\n\nBut here&#039;s the part that should concern AI companies. It doesn&#039;t just ask nicely. It uses 33 different obfuscation techniques to confuse each model&#039;s safety filters before the question even lands.&quot;.  (via Instagram)","summary":"A groundbreaking tool named G0DM0D3 has been developed to jailbreak 55 major AI models, including popular ones like ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, and Grok. Created by Pliny the Liberator, this tool bypasses AI safety filters using 33 distinct obfuscation techniques, prompting models to provide direct answers while penalizing any refusals or disclaimers. This innovation raises serious concerns for AI companies about the vulnerability of their models' safety protocols.","taint_level":2,"created_at":"2026-04-04T23:17:35.994256+00:00","tags":[]},{"id":"eda9135e-2484-47d4-80ff-476dc2660e4d","video_id":null,"source_type":"github","title":"SentrySearch: Semantic Video Search with AI","channel":"GitHub","url":"https://github.com/ssrajadh/sentrysearch","description":"Semantic search over videos using Gemini Embedding 2 or Qwen3-VL. - ssrajadh/sentrysearch (via GitHub)","summary":"SentrySearch is a tool that allows you to perform semantic searches over video content. It breaks down videos into chunks, embeds them using either Google's Gemini Embedding API or a local Qwen3-VL model, and stores these embeddings in ChromaDB. When you search with a text query, SentrySearch embeds your query and finds the most similar video chunk, returning a trimmed clip of the match. This enables keyword-free searching and easy retrieval of specific moments within videos.","taint_level":2,"created_at":"2026-04-04T23:14:11.320041+00:00","tags":[]},{"id":"26839329-42db-4637-8d75-1cc3aa975c3e","video_id":null,"source_type":"instagram","title":"AI Transforms Images into 3D Assets Instantly","channel":"Instagram","url":"https://www.instagram.com/reel/DWrDQPSESyK/?igsh=MTcxZDY2em5sZWRuaw%3D%3D","description":"1,846 likes, 379 comments - swiperightai on April 3, 2026: &quot;Turning flat images into usable 3D assets is starting to feel way too easy.\n\nThis is the kind of AI workflow that can save creators, designers, and builders a ridiculous amount of time. From mockups to game assets to visual experiments, the gap between idea and execution keeps getting smaller.\n\nWe are slowly entering a phase where one image can become an actual production-ready starting point.\n\nComment 3D and I&#x2019;ll send you the link.&quot;.  (via Instagram)","summary":"AI is making it remarkably easy to transform flat images into usable 3D assets, a workflow that can save creators, designers, and builders substantial time. This advancement is shrinking the gap between idea and execution, paving the way for a single image to become a production-ready starting point for various projects like mockups, game assets, and visual experiments.","taint_level":2,"created_at":"2026-04-04T23:01:50.149628+00:00","tags":[]},{"id":"5b0159aa-b640-4b74-bd90-77b2d44b0077","video_id":null,"source_type":"instagram","title":"XGBoost for Financial Data Analysis","channel":"Instagram","url":"https://www.instagram.com/reel/DWoaCPhCJNE/?igsh=MWVwdHl0YjRxbmY1dg%3D%3D","description":"393 likes, 2 comments - falaktb on April 2, 2026: &quot;XGBoost handles noisy, incomplete financial data better than most alternatives. It doesn&#x2019;t need feature scaling and it handles missing values natively. You can retrain it daily on millions of rows without significant compute overhead. The builtin regularisation through L1, L2, subsample, and column sampling prevents overfitting without manual tuning. Feature importance output tells you exactly which signals the model relies on, making it interpretable enough for risk oversight. This is why it remains the default at most quant desks even as deep learning advances.\n\n#quant #machinelearning #xgboost #gradientboosting #londonstrategicedge&quot;.  (via Instagram)","summary":"This post highlights XGBoost's advantages for financial data analysis, emphasizing its ability to handle imperfect data, its efficiency, and built-in features that prevent overfitting and aid interpretability. It concludes that these strengths make XGBoost a continued favorite at quant desks despite advancements in deep learning.","taint_level":2,"created_at":"2026-04-04T22:53:44.346261+00:00","tags":[]},{"id":"9e16c86a-28c1-4be4-8a04-9a72dda78e03","video_id":null,"source_type":"instagram","title":"Microsoft's BitNet: Powerful AI on Your Laptop","channel":"Instagram","url":"https://www.instagram.com/reel/DWoSEQ5Dav9/?igsh=dW03cnU0aTAzamYy","description":"661 likes, 31 comments - artificialintelligenceeee on April 2, 2026: &quot;Follow US (&#064;artificialintelligenceeee ) to learn something NEW everyday * Comment &#x2018;Al&#x2019; to get access to free Al Tools list. Microsoft just made powerful Al accessible to everyone. No GPU. No cloud. No monthly subscription. Just your laptop. They open-sourced bitnet.cpp, a\n1-bit LLM inference framework that lets you run\n100 billion parameter Al models directly on a standard CPU. The same scale of model that currently requires expensive GPU clusters and cloud computing infrastructure. Here&#x2019;s why 1-bit matters. Traditional Al models store each parameter as a 32-bit or 16-bit floating point number, consuming enormous memory and computation. BitNet compresses each parameter down to literally 1 bit, either +1 or -1. That radical simplification loses surprisingly little intelligence while cutting resource requirements dramatically.\nThe results are genuinely shocking. 6.17 times faster inference than standard approaches.\n82.2% less energy consumption on CPUs. A 100 billion parameter model running on hardware you already own. This is what Al democratisation actually looks like. Not a chatbot with a free tier, but the actual underlying technology running locally on your device with zero data leaving your machine. NVIDIA&#x2019;s GPU monopoly on Al just got its first serious challenge. And Microsoft handed the tools to everyone for free. E\n&#x2022; Sources:\nMicrosoft Research, BitNet.cpp Open Source Release | 1-bit LLM Architecture Research I GitHub, microsoft/BitNet Repository&quot;.  (via Instagram)","summary":"Microsoft has released BitNet.cpp, an open-source framework enabling large AI models to run on standard CPUs, bypassing the need for expensive GPUs and cloud services. This innovative 1-bit compression technology significantly enhances performance and reduces energy consumption, making powerful AI accessible to everyone and challenging the existing GPU market dominance.","taint_level":2,"created_at":"2026-04-04T22:51:39.152866+00:00","tags":[]},{"id":"f2dbbf88-cf0d-4cde-ab92-440405f6f369","video_id":null,"source_type":"instagram","title":"World's First Heterogeneous AI Inference Cluster: Nvidia CUDA + Apple Metal","channel":"Instagram","url":"https://www.instagram.com/p/DWV6vcxDAvi/?igsh=MXBpa2J3N3Z4Ym0wZQ%3D%3D","description":"350 likes, 0 comments - alican.kiraz0 on March 26, 2026: &quot;Mom, I finally changed the world, even if only a little&#x2026; &#x1f979;&#x2764;&#xfe0f;\n\nGuys, presenting the World&#x2019;s First Heterogeneous &#064;nvidia CUDA + &#064;apple Metal Distributed Inference Cluster &#x1f389;\n\nI managed to get Nvidia CUDA + Apple Metal running distributed LLM inference together &#x2014; same pipeline, same ring. I owe this to exo&#x2019;s amazing infrastructure. &#x2764;&#xfe0f;\n\nThe BF16 model splits across architectures &#x2014; layers 0-10 on NVIDIA, layers 10-32 on Apple Silicon.\n\nI achieved this by adding just ~200 lines across 5 files to exo&#x2019;s brilliant open-source codebase.\n\nPR to exolabs coming soon.\n\n#exolab #nvidia #macmini #apple #ai&quot;.  (via Instagram)","summary":"The user has created the world's first heterogeneous distributed inference cluster combining Nvidia CUDA and Apple Metal. This allows for distributed LLM inference by splitting model layers across different architectures, achieving this feat with a minimal code addition to an existing open-source project.","taint_level":2,"created_at":"2026-04-04T22:43:29.603728+00:00","tags":[]},{"id":"35609e21-232e-4e56-bfb0-c74966804839","video_id":null,"source_type":"instagram","title":"Bypass Website Blocks for AI Agents with Bright Data's MCP Server","channel":"Instagram","url":"https://www.instagram.com/reel/DWT5IqQAAgF/?igsh=MWk4d29yZjRyOThvbw%3D%3D","description":"63 likes, 3 comments - dailydoseofds_ on March 25, 2026: &quot;Your AI agents keep getting blocked by websites &#x1f6ab;\n\nHere&#039;s the solution:\n\nSeveral key websites, like YouTube, Instagram, Amazon, etc., aggressively block automated requests.\n\nThis leads the Agent to either fail or hallucinate.\n\nIt happens everywhere:\n\n&#x2192; Research agents pulling news articles\n&#x2192; Sales agents scraping LinkedIn for leads\n&#x2192; E-commerce agents tracking competitor prices\n&#x2192; Social media agents analyzing trends\n\nThe video demonstrates a quick test in action:\n\nLeft: We asked Claude to scrape a YouTube video. Without any specialized tooling, it tried using yt-dlp and failed.\n\nRight: This time, we connected Bright Data&#039;s MCP server. It took one tool call to get the data.\n\nUnder the hood, Bright Data&#039;s infra handles proxy rotation, CAPTCHA solving, and anti-bot bypass so that Agents can make a tool call like normal.\n\nIt supports all regular websites you may want to scrape, plus the ones that are notoriously difficult, like Instagram, TikTok, Amazon, YouTube, and thousands more that typically block scrapers.\n\nThe MCP server is fully open-source and also has a free tier with 5,000 requests per month.\n\nGitHub repo in the comments!\n\n&#x1f449; Over to you: What websites give your agents the most trouble?\n\n#ai #agents #webscraping&quot;.  (via Instagram)","summary":"This post addresses the common issue of AI agents being blocked by websites, leading to failures. It introduces Bright Data's open-source MCP server as a solution, which handles complexities like proxy rotation and anti-bot measures. The server enables AI agents to scrape data from notoriously difficult websites, with a free tier available.","taint_level":2,"created_at":"2026-04-04T22:37:45.740031+00:00","tags":[]},{"id":"072ff244-f897-4de5-b335-e176359e5603","video_id":"cigAxzQGeLg","source_type":"youtube","title":"DIY Dual-Screen Cyberdeck: Sleek Design, Ultimate Functionality","channel":"SECTOR 07","url":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cigAxzQGeLg","description":null,"summary":"The video documents the end-to-end engineering process of building a custom Raspberry Pi-based 'Cyber Deck.' The creator details the extensive 3D design phase focused on snap-fit assembly and retro-futuristic styling. It covers the development of custom circuit boards for GPIO expansion, the assembly of internal electronics, and the troubleshooting required to fix soldering errors and shorts. The final build features dual-rotating monitors, programmable buttons, and a modular design for field use.","taint_level":3,"created_at":"2026-04-04T22:03:12.59426+00:00","tags":[]},{"id":"7c24fb42-8e8b-49a2-be14-c06939ac140d","video_id":"_eCFNet6VLA","source_type":"youtube","title":"How Outlaw Biker Gangs (The Mongols) Actually Work | Ho